Nov 6 2008 	Delightful Respite	Hart House Hotel provided a delightful respite during our October visit to the London area. Our flight into LHR was significantly delayed, yet we were cheerfully greeted by Dana when we arrived at the hotel's doors after 10pm in the evening. We were ushered to a quiet, immaculate, pleasantly decorated, twin-bedded room with more than adequate space and facilities. There seem to be dozens of hotels in the area, running the range of price and amenities, but we highly recommend Hart House. Hotel employees are extremely helpful. We were treated with utmost courtesy and folks went out of their way to accommodate our stay. There is a &quot;free&quot; daily breakfast. One need not tote a PC as a computer is available for use by guests. For travellers with significant baggage or ambulatory issues, request a room on the first floor as an elevator is not available -- and would not, in any case, harmonize well with the boutique-style of the hotel. Further, if arriving at LHR, we recommend that one take the Heathrow Express to Paddington Station and a cab from there to Gloucester Place (Forget about going to Baker Street station). The hotel is located &quot;in the heart of London's West End&quot; (City of Westminster), with ready access to most traveller's needs within short walking distances; as are many of greater London's attractions (including Buckingham Palace). Pick up frequent city tours leaving Baker Street station. Owner/Manager Andrew readily dispenses helpful tourist advise. A great place! We look forward to a future stay. ~Richard &amp; Mae	
