Dec 6 2004	good place to stay	My daughters and I stayed at the Hart House Hotel the first week in November, 2004. It was in a gr8 location, between 2 tube lines, very clean and comfy. We had a room with 1 double and 1 single bed, fine for the 3 of us. It was small, no dresser, but very adequate. The breakfast was average, but a breakfast none-the-less, and the people were nice. It's not a hotel, so there's not a concierge that can direct you around, but we really enjoyed our stay there, and we were hardly ever there anyway, as we were tourists and gone all day touring! Stay there. It will be enjoyable and quiet.	
Aug 27 2004	Spotlessly Clean Smoke Free	This small hotel is basically a 16-room B&amp;B. All rooms have private baths and the breakfasts are terrific. We particularly liked the location: midway between Oxford Street and Regent's Park. This park may be London's best kept secret (beautiful well-kept gardens, open air theatre, excellent cafe). The London Zoo is at the far north-end of the park (world famous, but disappointing!). We also enjoyed the Wallace Collection, three blocks from the hotel: a better museum than the National Gallery, free admission (but do rent the audio tour), and a gorgeous cafe for lunch.	
